Open Tableau and connect to penglings.csv dataset.
Drag and drop 'Flipper Length' to the Columns shelf and 'Body Mass' to the Rows shelf.
Make sure that both axes are set to be continuous and that the scales do not start at 0.
From the 'Marks' panel, select the 'Circle' mark type.
Drag the 'Species' field to the Color mark to map the color to species.
Drag the 'Bill Length' field to the Size mark to map the size to bill length.
Adjust the opacity of the circles to 0.8 for a semi-transparent effect via the Color mark settings.
Ensure that both axes are properly labeled and that tick marks are set at reasonable intervals.
Add a title to the visualization.
Save workbook and export the visualization as an image.